cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with generating images of objects, handwritten digits, and sketches. It also proposes a novel GAN-based architecture for diverse and limited training data scenarios. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically Generative Adversarial Networks (GAN), which makes it likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

The paper's focus on learning the mixture model's parameters along with those of GAN suggests that it could also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. 

The paper's use of modified versions of "inception-score" to quantitatively characterize intra-class diversity of generated samples suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper's use of GANs to generate images could also make it relevant to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category.
